#Approach:

Maximum Product Subarray – Prefix Product + Suffix Product Approach

Is problem me maximum product nikalna hota hai, lekin yaha negative numbers aur zero ki wajah se problem tricky ho jaati hai.
Negative number product ka sign change kar sakta hai,
aur zero aane par product toot jata hai.

Isliye hum do directions me traversal karte hain:
ek prefix product (left se right)
aur ek suffix product (right se left)

Har step par:
pre ko current element se multiply karte hain
suf ko reverse side ke current element se multiply karte hain
aur answer ko pre aur suf me se maximum se update karte rehte hain.

Agar pre ya suf kabhi 0 ho jaye,
to usse 1 reset kar dete hain taki next subarray fresh start ho sake.

Prefix isliye zaroori hai kyunki max product normal left to right traversal me mil sakta hai.
Suffix isliye zaroori hai kyunki kabhi kabhi left side ka extra negative hataane par better answer right side se milta hai.

Is tarah hum saare important cases cover kar lete hain:
positive numbers, negative numbers, even/odd negatives, aur zero.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int maxProduct(int[] nums) {

        int n = nums.length;
        int pre = 1;
        int suf = 1;
        int ans = Integer.MIN_VALUE;

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if(pre == 0) pre = 1; 
            if(suf == 0) suf = 1;

            pre = pre * nums[i];
            suf = suf * nums[n-i-1];

            ans = Math.max(ans, Math.max(pre, suf));
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
